				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The reason why Druids and other classes are so effective with Kiting is because they have DoT(Duration over Time) spells that kill the mob while they are running.  A wizard does not have such spells.  We must stand still before we can get a shot off.  If you decide to use root, which you should, then you would get one good shot off, but then you are following the root blast blast root blast blast tactic.  Not kiting.  My suggestion for young wizards is to root the mob then blast.  It is a good, usually safe, tactic.  Problem occurs when you are fighting anything that can stun you.  Then you are in trouble.  You must fight for the Journeyman boots, they are no trade no drop.  A very good reason why they are so sought after.
