	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am a wizard of only level 18, but i have a little advice for all wizards.  Our class is the master of kill stealing.  My opinion is that kill stealing is when you watch someone attack something, wait until the creature gets upset with him or her, then go ahead and blast it and get the exp.  I have gotten people upset very often by getting the kill after responding to them call for help. (sometimes you forget just how much damage we can do in so little time :) ). However, ithink that in places like  Highpass or or the Tower in Crushbone, where there are so many people waiting for a spawn, we can get the most damage and take the loot as much as we want.  In this sort of situation, the 'kill' is as much yours as it is theirs.  The thing i dislike the most about everquest is that everyone likes to claim every mob as 'Theirs' and if you dare to kill it, you have stolen their kill.  When people yell at me for that kind of thing, i recommend you shrug them off.  Now then, people who like to use other people as tanks and take exp from something they couldnt POSSIBLY take solo, THEY should be shot.<BR>
- Also, some substantial advice...  I dont know if this is frowned upon by verant or other players, but kiting is a nice method for a wizard. We are not as good at it as a druid or enchanter, but for me it's VERY effective for killing evens and yellows.  Kiting, for those who have never heard of it, is when you get Spirit of wolf casted on you, then attack something with a spell (enchanters, druids, shamans use spells that do damage over time because it is more effective, but we have to use our direct damage spell), and run.  Hopefully the creature is slow (hehe), so you can get a good distance between you and the creature.   when you know you are far enough away, you stop and zap it with another spell, then run again. This is good for wizards because using this you never have to get hit, which is always important for us, with our pathetic hitpoints. But always make sure you have a lower level DD spell memorized, because if you get to low on mana to cast your best, you will probably still have enough to cast your second best, and that could save your life.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
